article.headline: Old Dominion 92, Georgia State 57
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Drew Williamson scored 14 points and Old Dominion had five players score in double figures Monday night in a 92-57 viuctory against Georgia State. The Monarchs (15-7, 8-3 Colonial Athletic Association) made their first five shots of the night, led 46-29 at halftime and coasted. Arnaud Dahi also scored 14, Brian Henderson and Gerald Lee had 12 each and Valdas Vasylius had 11. Georgia State (7-14, 3-8) shot just 36 percent and was 2-for-17 on 3-pointers. Old Dominion, by contrast, shot 51 percent and converted 9 of 17 tries from long range. Lance Perique led the Panthers with 16 points and Brandon Cartwright had 12.
